cause the Human-Machina recreated them.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MayflyDecemberRomance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MayflyDecemberRomance">Mayfly&#150;December Romance</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Soubi and his wife in the manga, as a result of him being Talisman's Factor and therefore not aging</span>. There's also a case of Mayfly December <em>Ship Teasing</em> in the anime between <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Jack and Risako</span>, but that gets torpedoed by the end of the anime.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Also Ishigami and his wife.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulName">Meaningful Name</a>: JUDA <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Ishigami used to work as Katou's right hand man (during <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/WorldWarII" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/WorldWarII">World War II</a>) before becoming the factor for the Machina JUDA, afterwards he betrayed the Katou Organization. The Machina JUDA itself is one; it had no default name or serial number, and instead called itself 'J-U-D-A' when prompted. It is the Judas of the Machina.</span><ul><li> Deus as well. It's introduced as simply "Deus", but then we learn the Human-Machina call it <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeusExMachina" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeusExMachina">Deus ex Machina</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MechaMooks" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MechaMooks">Mecha-Mooks</a>: Any Arma not being piloted by a named character is screwed.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MegaCorp" title="/pmwik